          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SISD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " a 50 mm*50 mm double sided silicon strip",
                "detector(Micron Semiconductors Ltd.) type-W"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MCPLT"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " To provide a local reference time for each ion",
                "delivered, a 3 mum aluminized mylar foil at 45 degree",
                "to the beam axis and a microchannel plate (MCP) were",
                "positioned upstream."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A 95 MeV/nucleon primary beam of 20Ne bombarded a thick",
                "carbon target. Secondary 18F ions were extracted in",
                "the molecular form HF, ionized in an ECR ion source,",
                "and postaccelerated with the CIME cyclotron to form a",
                "secondary radioactive ion beam of energy 3.924 MeV/",
                "nucleon"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A 5.5+-0.3 mum Au foil was mounted on the upstream face",
                "of the target ladder, degrading the 18F beam to an",
                "energy of 1.7 MeV/nucleon. The target then consisted of",
                " 55+-4 mum of low density PTFE (CH2 polymer), thick",
                "enough to stop the beam, but thin enough to allow light",
                "ions to escape."
              ]
            }
          ],
